11 An Act relating to environmental and natural
resources; exempting property that is part of the
12 Conservation Commission Cost-Share Program from
eminent domain; providing purpose for protection from
13 eminent domain; providing exceptions; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-3-118 of Title 27A, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 To protect natural resources and landowner rights, private lands
22 that are entered into the Cost-Share Program are exempt from eminent
23 domain. This protection will ensure the longevity of conservation
24 efforts, with exemptions granted only for eminent domain projects
Req. No. 16740 Page 1

1 esse ntial to safeguarding public health and including those projects
2 which involve the transmission or distribution of electricity or
3 natural gas.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
